spanishExample: Se casa y la boda es en ese lugar.
englishTranslation: She is getting married and the wedding is in that place.

spanishExample: Él no la amaba, pero yo la amo.
englishTranslation: He didn’t love her, but I love her.

spanishExample: Quiero dormir antes de la reunión.
englishTranslation: I want to sleep before the meeting.

spanishExample: Quiero que tenga éxito en la carrera.
englishTranslation: I want him to have success in the race.

spanishExample: Se iban a casar, pero están en una pelea.
englishTranslation: They were going to get married, but they are in a fight.

spanishExample: La boda es cerca de mi casa.
englishTranslation: The wedding is near my house.

spanishExample: Si te casas, serás feliz.
englishTranslation: If you get married, you will be happy.

spanishExample: La fiesta será en su casa, así que lleva canciones buenas.
englishTranslation: The party will be at his house, so bring good songs.

spanishExample: La casa está bonita, ¡esta fiesta será una sorpresa!
englishTranslation: The house is(Estar) pretty, this party will be a surprise!

spanishExample: Estás hermosa con esa ropa, pero recuerda que la fiesta no es en una casa.
englishTranslation: You’re gorgeous with those clothes, but remember that the party is not at a house.

spanishExample: Ella duerme mucho, pero igual la amas.
englishTranslation: She sleeps a lot, but you still love her.

spanishExample: Esta comida está buena, creo que fue hecha con mucho amor.
englishTranslation: This food is(Estar) good, I think it was made with a lot of love.

spanishExample: El negocio ha sido hecho por los dos hombres.
englishTranslation: The deal has been made by the two men.

spanishExample: Él aún está durmiendo, así que esto debe ser un error.
englishTranslation: He is still sleeping, so this must be a mistake.

spanishExample: Para su sorpresa, la música fue hecha sin letra.
englishTranslation: To their surprise, the music was made without lyrics.

spanishExample: La tarea es hecha por ella.
englishTranslation: The task is done by her.

spanishExample: No se le ocurrió una idea en caso de un ataque.
englishTranslation: He didn’t come up with an idea in case of an attack.

spanishExample: Me caso porque ella me ama.
englishTranslation: I’m getting married because she loves me.

spanishExample: El accidente fue triste.
englishTranslation: The accident was sad.

spanishExample: Él no se había casado.
englishTranslation: He hadn’t gotten married.

spanishExample: Está serio ahora porque está en una misión.
englishTranslation: He is serious now because he is on a mission.

spanishExample: Soy feliz y por eso terminé mi carrera.
englishTranslation: I am(Ser) happy and that’s why I finished my degree program.

spanishExample: Su carrera es triste y él lo sabe.
englishTranslation: His career is sad and he knows it.

spanishExample: No ha dormido y por eso no se le han ocurrido buenas ideas.
englishTranslation: He hasn’t slept and that’s why he hasn’t come up with good ideas.

spanishExample: No se le ocurre una buena letra para su nombre.
englishTranslation: He doesn’t come up with a good letter for his name.
